Daily vlogs for 30 days, let’s go 🥰❤️ I noticed I was genuinely triggered by the takeover of short-form content because I’ve done a certain kind of storytelling for 7 years now. I’ve decided instead of hating it, I will try it for real. At the end of 30 days, I can decide if to keep it going or to put it aside - but if you never try, you’ll never know!

Day 2/30 - I dont really know how to tell a story of an entire day in 1 and a half minutes but I’m going to keep trying until I get it or delete my entire social media presence on the internet. 😇 what do you want to see more of in my life?

Day 3 | I’ve struggled with PMDD since I was probably 12 years old. I was put on birth control for it at 14. It didn’t fix it but it made the time I struggled with it shorter. At 23, I got off birth control and over the years, the dysphoria got worse, the time it took over my life went from 3 days, to 7, to 10, and in the past year I’ve had to deal with it for two whole weeks out of the month before starting my cycle. I decided this year that it was time to really be proactive about it - now that I live with someone, I can’t hide from humanity for half the month and pray to make it through the dysphoria. I had to face my demons, and finally at 30 I’m seeing that it can be helped. I’m healing through foods, acupuncture, and herbs. So far I’ve had two cycles that were better in different ways than in the last year, but I’m definitely not “there” yet. I’ll keep updating you since I know I’m not alone in this ❤️

Is this going to work? Am I going to fail? Will all of this be for nothing?

These are some of the questions that come up when you are thinking about taking a leap of faith or committing to something beyond yourself.

Doubts are normal. Fear is natural.

What if the result didn’t matter? Would you still take the chance?

It’s not all about the end result, it’s who we become in the process.

I feel as if I’ve been knocking on the doorway to a new reality - my desired reality, for a few months now.

And finally, it has opened, and I’m walking through it.

When our outer circumstances do not align with what we desire on the inside, it’s really important to take a look at our belief systems and the stories we’re telling all day long.

A couple months ago I identified a few stories I was telling myself and others about myself, about others, about the world, and about my circumstances.

These stories were disempowering, and they were disguised by a desire to be modest & humble.

Take your disempowering stories and replace their masks with your own reasoning - perhaps insecurity, self-doubt, envy, self-abuse, or a desire to please others is keeping you stuck in these same stories. 

So I started knocking on the doorway of my mind, calling out to it with more empowering stories:

“I have everything that I need inside of myself, now.” “I’m already whole and fulfilled now.”

“I love myself as I am. I deserve love as I am.”

At first, reality might not change overnight - it can, for the pliable amongst us, but you have to consider that it took a while for these old stories to build in the realm of your mind, and it might take some time to knock them to the ground and build something more beautiful.

Now, I’m finally seeing it. When you notice one sign that life is shifting and changing in your favor, you’ll start to notice more. So look for those signs - look for the subtle ways that things begin going your way. Notice them and be grateful for them, because little by little, and then all at once, you’ll see it all change for the better.

“What must I give more death to today, in order to generate more life? What not-beauty do I fear? What should die today? What should live?” As we prune our inner garden, we have to take care to recognize that even the not-beautiful is useful. I don’t want to run from the not-beautiful. I want to face it head on, within me, within others, within my relationships. When I face the not-beautiful, I remember that the difference between a weed and a flower is perception, and that I need only shift my perception to find the beauty in the not-beautiful as well. And sometimes, we can prune and weed our garden. But it must be us in there, doing the work, facing it all head-on. What are the not-beautiful parts within yourself, your relationships, or your environment that you need to confront and acknowledge? Can you see how staying in the trenches will transform you?

Would you learn to use a weapon during war? No, you would learn during times of peace so that you may be a better warrior in battle. This has been my approach to cultivating peace lately. Becoming a peaceful warrior, to me, means training for peace and mindfulness - using whatever tools resonates with you, I.e. meditation, yoga, prayer, chanting, movement, creativity - during times of peace, so that you are better equipped to handle challenging times. It’s great to meditate when you’re anxious. But what if you meditate when you feel great, too? How are you training as a peaceful warrior? Help someone get inspired!! 🤍

✨ “What I desire desires me” - outer intention calls for switching our perspective. Instead of thinking we’re the only ones desiring something, we consider that the object of our desire is also longing for us.

Instead of feeling like we’re forcing, hustling and striving towards what we want, we consider that if something is searching for us like we are searching for it, we’ll meet in the harmonious, divine center. We let go of resistance because we’re not the only ones working toward receiving this thing - this thing is actually working towards us, as well. 

This doesn't mean we sit back and do nothing. We still take *inspired* action. But the difference lies in the feeling. It's about alignment, flow, and mutual attraction. When we believe that what we desire also desires us, the journey to manifest becomes more joyful, less stressful, and beautifully effortless.🍋🌸

“Fortune favors the bold” is not merely a saying, it’s a fact. Fortuna, Roman goddess of luck and prosperity, holding a cornucopia in one hand to symbolize abundance and a ship’s rudder in the other to symbolize control over destiny, has her favorites. Her favorites are the ones who, at least once in a while, throw caution to the wind, listen to their Deep Self (intuition) and follow their bliss. She comes to aid the ones who are willing to take chances. It’s okay to be safe and comfortable - but once in a while, take a leap of faith in yourself. Fortuna favors the bold, and the Universe (God) rewards bravery. Have a happy, healthy, prosperous week, I love you!

🤍A reminder that we attract what we are - and to attract love, we must become love, loving, lovers. To attract abundance, we must become abundance embodied. 

To become love, notice all the ways in your life you are already loved. Pay attention to all the things that YOU already love, already have to love. 

To become abundance, give of yourself generously (as long as you have enough to fill yourself up, too!). Give and spend what you do have plenty of freely - time, attention, love, devotion. Give out compliments easy. Say thank you and appreciate the things in your life that you’re grateful for.

*Become* what you desire.
